FunctionNormalizers - Interface in testHelp
One of two interfaces - the other is UnboundMethodNormalizers - with no abstract methods that bundle static methods which normalize specialized functions and unbound methods which take arguments and/or return values of primitive types (boolean, double, int, long) to generic functions and methods which take arguments and return values of the corresponding object types (Boolean, Double, Integer, Long).
